{
    "name": "Smith",
    "type": "npc",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Smith",
            "type": "section",
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 245",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 245",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 245
                }
            ],
            "html": "Most smaller communities have at least one smithy where locals and travelers can have horses shod or equipment repaired. Larger settlements and cities often have a variety of smiths, many specializing in blacksmithing, weapon smithing, armor smithing, or even smelting coins in a mint. The smith is a 6th-level challenge when competing with smithing or other crafting tasks.<br/><br/><b><u><a aonid=\"5\" game-obj=\"Skills\" general=\"true\">Recall Knowledge - Humanoid</a></u> (<u><a aonid=\"14\" game-obj=\"Skills\">Society</a></u>)</b>: DC 18"
        },
        {
            "name": "Tradespeople",
            "type": "section",
            "sections": [
                {
                    "name": "Common Artisan Guilds",
                    "type": "section",
                    "sources": [
                        {
                            "type": "source",
                            "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                            "link": {
                                "type": "link",
                                "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 244",
                                "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 244",
                                "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                            },
                            "page": 244
                        }
                    ],
                    "subtype": "sidebar",
                    "sidebar_type": "additional_lore",
                    "sidebar_heading": "Additional Lore",
                    "image": {
                        "type": "image",
                        "name": "Additional Lore",
                        "image": "Sidebar_2_AdditionalLore.png"
                    },
                    "html": "Cartographers <br/>Cobblers <br/>Cooks and bakers <br/>Glassblowers <br/>Herbalists <br/>Jewelers and gem cutters <br/>Leatherworkers <br/>Locksmiths <br/>Magecrafters <br/>Masons and stonecutters <br/>Painters and sign makers<br/>Physicians and apothecaries <br/>Potion brewers <br/>Potters <br/>Scroll keepers <br/>Shipwrights and sailmakers <br/>Skinners and tanners <br/>Wagonmakers and wheelwrights <br/>Weaponsmiths <br/>Wandcrafters <br/>Weavers <br/>Woodcarvers and coopers"
                }
            ],
            "sources": [
                {
                    "type": "source",
                    "name": "Gamemastery Guide",
                    "link": {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 244",
                        "alt": "Gamemastery Guide pg. 244",
                        "href": "https://paizo.com/products/btq01zq7"
                    },
                    "page": 244
                }
            ],
            "html": "Every settlement needs tradespeople to create new products, facilitate commerce, and keep the infrastructure from crumbling. Larger cities often have entire guilds dedicated to the creation of specific goods, managing worker conditions, and working with local governments."
        }
    ],
